The numbers on each run directory carry hidden meaning:

RUN_0* are the nominal model tests; these runs generate data that can be
automatically compared against the data in the verif_data directory.

RUN_1* are off-nominal runs that result in specific error messages.  These
should be manually checked to confirm that the intended error message is
getting broadcast.

RUN_2* are failure cases.  In these cases the configuration results in
simulation termination.  These should be manually checked to confirm that the
error messages match expectation.
